criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Be at least 18 years;

          -  Present at least 4 NCCLs in vital teeth with margins in enamel and dentin (and its
             largest area in dentin), independently of teeth location;

          -  Non-smoking;

          -  Read and sign the Statement of Informed Consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Compromised medical history;

          -  Severe or chronic periodontitis;

          -  Extreme caries sensitivity;

          -  Heavy bruxism;

          -  Under orthodontic treatment;

          -  Poor oral hygiene;

          -  Smokers.
